{"TopicId":91282,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"For Questions That Don\u0026#039;t Merit Their Own Thread","CreatedByName":"Skyler4856","CreatedById":76452,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-26T04:12:34Z","PageNum":293,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-17T20:21:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647548206\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://allabouteyes.com/see-past-fascinating-history-eyeglasses/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://allabouteyes.com/see-past-fascinating-history-eyeglasses/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, only in 1700s they first realized that the ears are created to tie small things to them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose who don\u0027t know history are doomed to recreate it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T13:41:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is water noisy as \u00A0it heats to boil, and then gets quiet immediately before the boil, yet is appropriately loud when it is boiling?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T13:55:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647610886\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is water noisy as \u00A0it heats to boil, and then gets quiet immediately before the boil, yet is appropriately loud when it is boiling?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nscience?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T14:29:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause before it boils, the upper layer of the water is cool, so the bubbles implode on touching it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd then they explode only on the hot surface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T15:46:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647548476\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose who don\u0027t know history are doomed to recreate it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd when they recreate it, they think it is something totally new and different.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647610886\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is water noisy as \u00A0it heats to boil, and then gets quiet immediately before the boil, yet is appropriately loud when it is boiling?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve thought about this, too, especially when I make my daily bowl of instant grits or oatmeal or my evening hot green tea. It\u0027s really a fascinating thing about the properties of water, something we take for granted.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103892\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647613745\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause before it boils, the upper layer of the water is cool, so the bubbles implode on touching it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd then they explode only on the hot surface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, sorta. As for the noise, it\u2019s caused by\u003Cstrong\u003E cavitation\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a high-tech way of saying bubbles form and then they pop. When you heat water on the stove, the layer at the bottom is the first to boil, meaning it turns into a gas. The water vapor collects into bubbles, which rise toward the surface, passing through cooler water en route. (Google for the win! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Entropian","CreatedById":205453,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T19:21:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103907\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647618388\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd when they recreate it, they think it is something totally new and different.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027all want to join me in invading Russia in winter?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-22T22:33:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat causes Hawking radiation\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T00:10:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEntropy?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T01:11:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103976\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647631264\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205453\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Entropian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/18/2022 at 8:21 PM, Entropian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027all want to join me in invading Russia in winter?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but doing it from the east should work\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Entropian","CreatedById":205453,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T02:50:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647997913\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but doing it from the east should work\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe probably should pull a Genghis and invade when it\u0027s warmer though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SOXBLOX","CreatedById":204106,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T04:37:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105608\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647988435\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat causes Hawking radiation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it happens because of the particles and anti-particles that spontaneously generate in all of space. (That\u0027s the reason you can never have truly empty space.) Normally, they cancel out, and nobody notices them, but when they pop up near a black hole, sometimes one particle is pulled in, and the other gets away. The flow of escaping particles is what we call Hawking radiation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone who knows better, please correct me if I\u0027m wrong!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T06:14:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105676\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648003813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205453\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Entropian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Entropian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe probably should pull a Genghis\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EBaron von Ungern has entered the chat\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T07:07:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105662\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647997913\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but doing it from the east should work\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are going to free the Vinland from Saxen?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Just watching the globe of Norway.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SSTO Crasher","CreatedById":215483,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T12:15:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105697\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648010274\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204106\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SOXBLOX\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, SOXBLOX said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it happens because of the particles and anti-particles that spontaneously generate in all of space. (That\u0027s the reason you can never have truly empty space.) Normally, they cancel out, and nobody notices them, but when they pop up near a black hole, sometimes one particle is pulled in, and the other gets away. The flow of escaping particles is what we call Hawking radiation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone who knows better, please correct me if I\u0027m wrong!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I still don\u2019t know why that causes the black hole to evaporate nor do I know why the process speeds up over time\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T12:45:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105794\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648037705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I still don\u2019t know why that causes the black hole to evaporate nor do I know why the process speeds up over time\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis may help out.\u00A0 The intro covers the basics of it, but he goes on a deeper dive:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/qPKj0YnKANw?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Terwin","CreatedById":139655,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-23T13:02:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224105794\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648037705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022215483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SSTO Crasher\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Crasher said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I still don\u2019t know why that causes the black hole to evaporate nor do I know why the process speeds up over time\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe spontaneously creating/destroying particles(called virtual particles I believe) will normally attract each other and annihilate, returning the \u0027borrowed\u0027\u00A0 energy they came from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there is a steep enough force gradient, one of these particles can be turned from it\u0027s course and instead follow the gradient(in the case of black holes, this would be gravity of course, with smaller black holes having a steeper gradient).\u00A0 With a black hole, the particle that is sucked in can never re-combine with it\u0027s sister particle, turning that sister particle from virtual to real.\u00A0 Because the energy to \u0027create\u0027 that new real particle must come from somewhere, the energy is considered to come from the black hole(presumably the sister-particle that falls in will annihilate with a particle inside the black hole, reducing the energy of the black hole)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I\u0027m guessing the video explains this better however)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T14:28:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.cnn.com/2022/03/24/world/odd-radio-circles-space-scn/index.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.cnn.com/2022/03/24/world/odd-radio-circles-space-scn/index.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI swear I have seen that image on the screen of the original series of Star Trek.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T14:31:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you have a \u0022star\u0022 made entirely of uranium? Somehow a cloud of uranium isotope ratio TBD collapses and forms an object that emits roughly the same power as the sun for an appreciable length of time. A reasonable proportion of the energy needs to come from fission rather than just gravitational collapse a-la \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelvin%E2%80%93Helmholtz_mechanism\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelvin\u2013Helmholtz_mechanism\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think an equivalent question is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a negative feedback mechanism in the collapse of a cloud of uranium that will result in a steady power output.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T14:41:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably you mean this one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002257801\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1794165304\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/207381-cosmic-anomaly-discussion/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4105939\u0026amp;embedComment=4105939\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:295px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T14:59:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224106271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648132882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably you mean this one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002257801\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8890942512\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/207381-cosmic-anomaly-discussion/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4105939\u0026amp;embedComment=4105939\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:342px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion Inspired by that post but that star just has some uranium in its atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hyperspace Industries","CreatedById":212417,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T15:04:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you make a hot air balloon which was painted black, or transparent and working like a car in the sun, that heated itself with sunlight? (This might be able to reduce the mass of hot air balloons, allowing more payload.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T15:12:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224106282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648134241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212417\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hyperspace Industries\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Hyperspace Industries said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you make a hot air balloon which was painted black, or transparent and working like a car in the sun, that heated itself with sunlight? (This might be able to reduce the mass of hot air balloons, allowing more payload.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably, but why would you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hyperspace Industries","CreatedById":212417,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T15:18:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224106291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648134753\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210816\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Admiral Fluffy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Admiral Fluffy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably, but why would you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe gains are probably meaningless, but it is an idea, and I like to think and figure stuff out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe main benefit would be probably just fuel costs, and even that is minor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-03-24T15:19:11Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2022 03:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Hyperspace Industries\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Terwin","CreatedById":139655,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T15:22:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224106293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648135083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212417\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hyperspace Industries\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Hyperspace Industries said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe gains are probably meaningless, but it is an idea, and I like to think and figure stuff out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe main benefit would be probably just fuel costs, and even that is minor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the cost is not having control over your buoyancy, which seems pretty major.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(needing to wait until the air in your balloon is sun-heated also means waiting until the ambient air is also warmer and presumably reducing lift)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-24T15:31:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224106282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002291282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221648134241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212417\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hyperspace Industries\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Hyperspace Industries said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you make a hot air balloon which was painted black, or transparent and working like a car in the sun, that heated itself with sunlight? (This might be able to reduce the mass of hot air balloons, allowing more payload.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I was a child I bought a present for a friend which was basically an enormous black plastic bag and a light string, you filled the bag with air and waited for it to take off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}